entry.tran: 社交聚会常客；特定聚会的参加者
entry.def: A party-goer is someone who likes going to parties or someone who is at a particular party.

example.ex: Chants from the drunken party-goers woke residents and the police were called...
example.tran: 酩酊大醉的聚会者唱歌吵醒了居民，有人报了警。

example.ex: At least half the partygoers were under 15.
example.tran: 这些参加聚会的人中至少有一半不到15岁。

means.word_mean: 1. someone who is attending a party;
